{% block content %}
    <div class="intro scroll-row">
        <div id="subhead">Admissions and Financial Aid</div>
        <p>Part II of The Crimson&#39;s Class of 2017 Survey examines admissions and financial aid at Harvard. According to reports from the survey, the average Harvard freshman receives financial aid, comes from a household that earns between $125,000 and $250,000 per year, and scored a 2237 on the SAT. Average standardized test scores varied by ethnicity and income, as well as varsity status&mdash;recruited athletes, on average, scored 173 points lower on the SATs than their non-recruited classmates.</p>
        <p>About 14 percent of the incoming freshman said their families earn above $500,000 per year, putting them among the top 1 percent of earners in the United States.</p>
        <p>Read Part II of The Crimson's four-part series on the freshman survey <a href="http://www.thecrimson.com/article/2013/9/4/freshman-survey-admissions-aid/">here</a>.</p>
    </div>

